==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eupittone
<hw>Eu*pit"tone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>eu-</ets> + <ets>pitt</ets>acal + <ets>-one</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A yellow, crystalline substance, resembling
aurin, and obtained by the oxidation of pittacal; -- called also
<altname>eupittonic acid</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>eupitton</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eupittonic</ent>⟦br⟧
